---
import Link from "../components/Link.astro";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | Fue Her"
  description="Learn about Fue Her, a full-stack engineer focused on accessible interfaces, reliable systems, and thoughtful web product development."
>
  <main class="py-12 sm:py-20">
    <section class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-sm font-bold uppercase text-[#366CC6] dark:text-[#E05243]">
        About
      </p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-black text-stone-950 sm:text-5xl dark:text-stone-50">
        Hi, I&apos;m Fue.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300">
        My name is pronounced /fu:/, like &quot;food&quot; without the
        &quot;d&quot;. I&apos;m a full-stack engineer who likes building clear,
        useful software with teams that care about both people and craft.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="mt-12 grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[0.72fr_1.28fr]">
      <aside class="h-fit rounded-md border border-stone-300 bg-stone-100/70 p-5 dark:border-stone-800 dark:bg-stone-900/70">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-black text-stone-950 dark:text-stone-50">
          How I Work
        </h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm leading-6 text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300">
          <li>Understand the core problem before reaching for an implementation.</li>
          <li>Identify the user, product, and technical requirements that shape the work.</li>
          <li>Break the solution into clear, testable pieces that can ship responsibly.</li>
          <li>Implement in a maintainable way, with accessibility, reliability, and future changes in mind.</li>
        </ul>
      </aside>

      <section class="space-y-8">
        <article>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-stone-950 dark:text-stone-50">
            Background
          </h2>
          <div class="mt-3 space-y-4 leading-8 text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300">
            <p>
              Technology has always been a passion of mine, and I made a
              professional transition into the field in 2019. Since then,
              I&apos;ve been fortunate to work with supportive teams at both a
              start-up and a large corporation.
            </p>
            <p>
              My skills lean frontend, but my focus has always been full-stack:
              building reliable, accessible, and performant systems that can
              scale. I believe there&apos;s always room for improvement and
              something new to learn, so you might catch me trying out new tools
              and patterns along the way.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-stone-950 dark:text-stone-50">
            Outside Code
          </h2>
          <div class="mt-3 space-y-4 leading-8 text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300">
            <p>
              When I&apos;m not coding, you&apos;ll probably still find me at
              the computer playing video games, reading the latest web novel
              I&apos;m following, or watching my favorite
              <Link href="https://www.dropout.tv/game-changer" target="_blank" class="group">
                Game Changer.
                <img
                  src="/sam.png"
                  alt=""
                  height="100"
                  width="108"
                  aria-hidden="true"
                  class="absolute bottom-0 right-0 -z-10 opacity-0 transition-opacity duration-1000 group-focus:z-10 group-focus:opacity-100 group-hover:z-10 group-hover:opacity-100"
                />
              </Link>
            </p>
            <p>
              Away from a screen, I spend time with my partner gardening,
              cooking, or taking in nature on a hike.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
